---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '~/components/PageHero.astro';
import SectionDivider from '~/components/SectionDivider.astro';
import { site, contact } from '~/lib/site';

const updated = 'July 21, 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Inclusion Oriented collects, uses, and protects the information you share through our website."
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy Policy" />

  <SectionDivider />

  <section class="bg-white py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="legal mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <p class="!mt-0 text-sm font-medium text-steel">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <p>
          {site.legalName} (&ldquo;{site.name},&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;)
          respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect through
          our website at <a href={site.url}>{site.url.replace('https://', '')}</a> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;),
          how we use it, and the choices you have. By using the Site, you agree to this policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <h3>Information you provide</h3>
        <p>
          When you submit a form on our Site — such as our Request Services, Apply, or Volunteer
          forms — we collect the information you choose to give us. Depending on the form, this may
          include your name, email address, phone number, city, the name and date of birth of a
          person who may receive services, the services you&rsquo;re interested in, and any details
          you include in your message.
        </p>
        <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
        <p>
          Our hosting provider automatically logs limited technical information (such as IP address,
          browser type, and pages visited) to operate and secure the Site. We do <strong>not</strong>
          use advertising or third-party tracking cookies on this Site.
        </p>

        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to your inquiries and requests for services or information;</li>
          <li>To review and follow up on job applications and volunteer interest;</li>
          <li>To provide, coordinate, and administer our services;</li>
          <li>To maintain, secure, and improve the Site; and</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we share information</h2>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information. We share it only:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>With service providers</strong> that help us operate the Site — for example, our
            website host (Cloudflare) and our email-delivery provider (Resend), which transmits your
            form submission to our team. These providers process information on our behalf.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>When required by law</strong>, or to protect the rights, safety, and property of
            our organization, the people we serve, or others.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Information about children and the individuals we serve</h2>
        <p>
          Our services support individuals with disabilities, who may include minors. A parent,
          guardian, case manager, or authorized representative may submit information about a person
          who would receive services. We handle that information in accordance with this policy. The
          Site is not directed to children for the purpose of collecting personal information
          directly from them.
        </p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We keep the information you submit for as long as needed to respond to your request,
          provide our services, and meet our legal, tax, and recordkeeping obligations, after which
          we take reasonable steps to delete or de-identify it.
        </p>

        <h2>How we protect your information</h2>
        <p>
          Information submitted through the Site is transmitted over an encrypted (HTTPS) connection,
          and we use reasonable administrative and technical safeguards to protect it. However, no
          method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute
          security.
        </p>

        <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
        <p>
          You may request to review, correct, or delete the personal information you&rsquo;ve shared
          with us, or ask us to stop contacting you, by emailing
          <a href={contact.emailHref}>{contact.email}</a> or calling
          <a href={contact.phoneHref}>{contact.phone}</a>. We will respond consistent with applicable law.
        </p>

        <h2>Links to other websites</h2>
        <p>
          The Site links to third-party resources (such as the Nebraska Department of Health and
          Human Services and partner organizations). We are not responsible for the privacy
          practices or content of those websites; please review their policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we&rsquo;ll revise the
          &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above. Your continued use of the Site after changes take
          effect constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy or your information? Contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: <a href={contact.emailHref}>{contact.email}</a></li>
          <li>Phone: <a href={contact.phoneHref}>{contact.phone}</a></li>
          <li>Mail: {site.legalName}, {contact.address.street}, {contact.address.city}, {contact.address.state} {contact.address.zip}</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
